[SN]TITLE[SN]
Somalia's 60-year-old graduate motivated by feminist issues

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Sixty-year-old Safiyo Jama Gayre has just graduated in Somalia. She chose to study Sharia and secular law at Puntland State University in order to help victims of oppression, especially women.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
5 October 2016 Last updated at 17:54 BST
As the university's oldest female graduate, she says age should not be a barrier for education.
This is part a regular series on African Women You Need to Know.
Video journalist: Maryam Ghanbarzadeh
